[src:dependency-pinning/dependency-hell] Many software libraries are written in a generous way, in an attempt to fulfill most users' needs, but sometimes only a small portion of functions are required in the host code.
[src:dependency-pinning/dependency-hell] By examining the source, the functionality can be rewritten in a much more compact way (with respect to the license).
[src:dependency-pinning/dependency-hell] In general, this can significantly reduce the application code, reduce later maintenance costs, and improve the software writing skills of programmers.
